<div id="review_1391903" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1391903" />
    <a title="Kelly" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/94602-kelly"><img alt="Kelly" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1521304176p2/94602.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1391903?book_show_action=true">May 23, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kelly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kelly" href="/user/show/94602-kelly">Kelly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Kay fans, historical fantasy fans, epic lovers</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/94602-kelly?shelf=fantasy-and-scifi">fantasy-and-scifi</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/94602-kelly?shelf=owned">owned</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/94602-kelly?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/94602-kelly?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/94602-kelly?shelf=grande-dames">grande-dames</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1391903" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11871865707590058182">I&apos;m reminded of something, thinking of this book. I was reading the Unbearable Lightness of Being recently, and there was a motif introduced from a piece of Beethoven&apos;s. &quot;En muss sein!&quot; or, translated, &quot;It must be!&quot;. In other words, a &apos;heavy&apos; (as Kundera would have put it) sense of your own life and destiny. All the characters have that here, but in such a way that you love them for it, you don&apos;t want to hurt them for being pompous as is occasionally a problem in epic adventures. It&apos;s all about </span>
  <span id="freeText11871865707590058182" style="display:none">I'm reminded of something, thinking of this book. I was reading the Unbearable Lightness of Being recently, and there was a motif introduced from a piece of Beethoven's. "En muss sein!" or, translated, "It must be!". In other words, a 'heavy' (as Kundera would have put it) sense of your own life and destiny. All the characters have that here, but in such a way that you love them for it, you don't want to hurt them for being pompous as is occasionally a problem in epic adventures. It's all about fate and duty, but choice, too. Again, simply, but beautifully written, so I could understand it as a young teenager, and re-read it lovingly now.</span>
