        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer109411311" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14308855920042104702">Wow. I don&apos;t even know what to say. I&apos;m speechless! This was only my second Kay novel, the first being A Song for Arbonne, and I didn&apos;t really know what to expect. I have to admit, the blurb didn&apos;t really catch me... But I had found it in a used book store for cheap, so I decided to try it out. I am so glad I did!<br/><br/>I have to be very careful not to spoil it... It&apos;s hard not to gush though. The ending was so heart breaking, yet at the same time so beautiful and hopeful. The entire book was wonderful</span>
  <span id="freeText14308855920042104702" style="display:none">Wow. I don't even know what to say. I'm speechless! This was only my second Kay novel, the first being A Song for Arbonne, and I didn't really know what to expect. I have to admit, the blurb didn't really catch me... But I had found it in a used book store for cheap, so I decided to try it out. I am so glad I did!<br /><br />I have to be very careful not to spoil it... It's hard not to gush though. The ending was so heart breaking, yet at the same time so beautiful and hopeful. The entire book was wonderfully written. I really fell in love with the characters, and that's something that is very important to me.<br /><br />I'm not just giving this five stars.. I'm giving it six! It needs to be more than five. According to GR, five stars means "It was amazing". But this was more than amazing for me. Lots of books can be amazing, and you can absolutely love them. But it's more that "let's just be friends" kind of love for the most part (for me at least). You read them, love and appreciate them, put them back on the shelf, and move on. But this book.. This book I fell in love with. Like long walks on the beach love.<br /><br />And that's all I can really say. For me at least, this just moved onto my "favorite's" list for sure.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14308855920042104702" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


